Hello,
please, could you add a simple C++ example program of GLAD working with GLX and a simple X lib window in the example folder ?

I have much trouble trying to do just that, and no luck searching.
As soon as I include glad_glx.h instead of the GL/gl.h and glx.h classic headers in a X11 project, it immediately crashes (segmentation fault), because glad re-#defines all the glX functions (eg. glXQueryVersion), and they become uninitialized function pointers when including glad_glx.h.

Calling gladLoadGLX(<my_display>, <my_screen>) doesn't help...
But glXQueryVersion is one of the very first things my program does, so I need it working. What should I do ? I'm a bit lost.

I tried to isolate the issue in a minimal example but came across other problems.

I started from the minimal OpenGL + X11 program found [here](https://www.opengl.org/discussion_boards/showthread.php/165856-Minimal-GLX-OpenGL3-0-example?p=1178905&viewfull=1#post1178905), which works well.

But trying to add Glad to the mix, it doesn't compile anymore (more details below).
I generated glad GLX 1.4 debug files with the web interface. But trying to compile with them throws me compile errors like `undefined reference to 'glad_debug_glClearColor'` and `undefined reference to 'glad_debug_glClear'`.

What can I do from here ? If I try to add, for instance, an OpenGL 4.5 Core glad.c to the project, I now have errors because of `multiple definitions of glad_set_pre_callback`, because both the glad.c and glad_glx.c will define it...

Can you help me understand how to use glad in this situation ?
If I can get it working I'd even be glad (ha!) to make a PR to add it to the example/ folder myself !


---------------------------------
To quickly reproduce:
 my failing compile command is like `g++ glad/src/glad_glx.c glad/glad.c gl3.cpp -o gl3 -lX11 -lGL -ldl -I glad/include -I.`

