There seems to be a problem when trying to declare multiple groups with different BGP peers and processes definition: all processes are receiving all messages from all groups. 

Let's say you have the following ExaBGP configuration:

```
group group1 {
  process external1 {
    encoder json;
    peer-updates;
    neighbor-changes;
    receive-routes;
    run external.py;
  }
  neighbor 10.140.0.1 {
    router-id 192.168.37.128;
    local-address 192.168.37.128;
    local-as 65501;
    peer-as 65500;
    family {
      inet4 unicast;
      inet6 unicast;
    }
  }
}
group group2 {
  process external2 {
    encoder json;
    peer-updates;
    neighbor-changes;
    receive-routes;
    run external.py;
  }
  neighbor 10.140.0.2 {
    router-id 192.168.37.128;
    local-address 192.168.37.128;
    local-as 65501;
    peer-as 65500;
    family {
      inet4 unicast;
      inet6 unicast;
    }
  }
}
```

